cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SD

This paper involves the creation and analysis of a dataset for computational humor, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the development of classifiers for predicting humor, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves crowdsourcing and human evaluation, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SD (Sound) respectively.
